Articles.Content:
Hi, @apholis, and welcome aboard! I'm sorry to hear that KSP is giving you problems.

I've taken the liberty to put your error log in a spoiler for convienience. In the future, please upload logs to a third-party site, such as Dropbox, and link to them. The forum can't handle massive amounts of text, like you'd find in a log.

Best of luck!
can anyone tell me what wrong with it?

Hi @apholis,

do you use L-Tech Mod?

On 4/22/2017 at 11:38 AM, apholis said:

can anyone tell me what wrong with it?

Version 1.2.9 is on prerelease state and mods won't work wht this version yet.

14 minutes ago, Noobton said:

Version 1.2.9 is on prerelease state and mods won't work wht this version yet.

that's the only problem with it? if i downgrade it will the mods work?
it depends on the mod, but the most popular are compatible with 1.2.2

1 hour ago, Noobton said:

it depends on the mod, but the most popular are compatible with 1.2.2

the only one i really want to use is mechjeb, how do i downgrade it though? is it possible?
Mechjeb works, right click on Steam, properties, Betas -None - opt out of all betas

I have experienced the same problem. I am unable to use Mechjeb in version 1.2.9, even though it is listed as compatible in CKAN. I prefer KER, but that's not working either. They both cause CTD during the loading screen for me.

Easy fix: I'm just using version 1.2 until the pre-release gets... released, and the mods get updated.
